title: Heavy duty, beautiful handmade leather handbag!
text: This is a beautiful handmade bag/satchel/purse, crafted in India of goat leather.  As stated, it  measures 11x9x2.5 inches.  There are two buckles on the front which have magnetic metal snaps for closure.  There is a zippered compartment on the backside and a large slip in pocket on the front, under the flap and buckle closures.  Inside the purse, are two large slip in pockets (like purse dividers) and a large zippered compartment spanning the width of the purse.  The inside of my purse is a green colored canvas material.  I think the stitching is superb.  The adjustable shoulder strap is longer than 4 feet., close to 4.5ft.  It has excellent quality thick metal carabiners on the ends to attach to the D-rings on the sides of the satchel, and has a buckle to attach in the middle to adjust the length of the strap, so you can use as cross body, shoulder bag or underarm.  It feels like a saddlebag, - although being stiff and of thick leather, it is quite bendable and easily accessible.  I received a nice note inside the bag, explaining some of the qualities of the satchel, the handmade process and the progression of the leather softening and it taking on a leather patina as it ages.  I think it will look great with jeans.  I believe it's a great price for the quality, should last a long time and I would highly recommend.  It would make a great gift.

title: A Bit Greasy For The Face
text:
I've been making my own waterless skin care products for nearly 2 decades. This is what I tend to call a salve due to it's consistency, which is thin & greasy (it is solid, but it goes on thin, not creamy). It is okay for overnight use, but under makeup it's rather unpleasant. A teensy amount is all that is required when applied to the face.

The ingredients are fine, but not organic. The jar is nice. It's amber glass with a silver metal screw top. The jar is reusable & I know I will be doing just that.

The smell is fine. Frankincense is a great essential oil for aging skin.

If I had realized this would be so greasy, I would have never ordered it. It is a tad too greasy for the summer & high humidity & it is still a tad too greasy & not moisturizing enough in the winter with extremely low humidity. This is fine as a hand, foot, & skin salve, but not for the face.

While I like that this is handmade, I probably would not order it again.

title: Good quality kit, lacking instructions
text:
I got this kit for a friend's daughter back in November. After much hesitation this weekend my friend brought this back to me and said she couldn't figure it out. Her daughter is 7 at the moment and even with Mom's help, it was just too complicated. I am an experienced crafter and I could not follow the instructions. The instructions for this kit came on 1 side of a small half sheet of card, the other side featured a photo of a finished version. There was a total of 3 pictures for how to do a traditional webbing weave and they did not show the most important part, which was how to loop the thread. I had to go and look up a youtube tutorial.

Once I found the tutorial the weaving was pretty easy. if they can't provide better instructions they need to link to a youtube tutorial or something similar on their site.

Otherwise I find the materials plentiful and of good quality. Pretty colors. I did not particularly like the paper feathers. They were pretty but did not fit with the more natural theme of the rest of the dream catcher.

I would recommend caution when giving this o any child under high school age...you are likely going to have to do it yourself. So just be aware of that.

title: Pop Culture Art at its Finest
text:
I've had the "I LOVE LUCY" diorama for awhile, and I just added "BRADY BUNCH" to go along with it on my ever-growing wall of pop-art & TV.

These are very well designed and constructed. The artist took liberties with the perspectives of the actual TV sets and made them to conform to a one-size frame. This is great because you can collect them and they look awesome together. Their unique perspectives is also what makes them so unique and real art, in my opinion. (I have a BA in Art History. Don't laugh!) They clearly represent the TV sets they come from, but with a unique twist. They are so one-of-a-kind.

I love that this one (I LOVE LUCY) is in black-and-white! I read that the actual set WAS in B & W (wardrobe and makeup too) because Lucy and Desi wanted total accuracy for filming in B & W. Now that I've added the Brady Bunch, in color, they look so sharp together.

If TV ever becomes 3D, I don't know what the artist will do...start making them in 4D?!

title: One of A Kind Art--None of Your Friends Will Have One!

I love having my guests try and guess what shows they represent. They are totally worth the money because they are handmade to order and have lots of detail. The frames seem to be of high quality, too. They look great on my wall of pop culture & TV.
